THE Scheme couple James McMurray and Kerry Tomlin have been convicted of attacking their neighbour. Scheme pair in attack rap THE Scheme couple James McMurray and Kerry Tomlin have been convicted of attacking their neighbour.McMurray, 29, punched William Turnbull repeatedly on the head after he went into the couple's flat in Kilmarnock while Tomlin was in the bath.Tomlin, 32, wielded a knife at their victim the day after the January incident.At Kilmarnock Sheriff Court McMurray was jailed for six months. Tomlin was given four months. 